Replication Code for "Redefining shared information: a heterogeneity-adaptive framework for meta-analysis""

Required Packages:
Matrix
dplyr
numDeriv
purrr 
tidyr 
MASS  
nloptr
Hmisc
mvmeta
extraDistr
stringr
xtable
ggplot2
scales
janitor 
readr 
gridExtra
cowplot 
ggokabeito

File Structure and Instructions:
- "functions.R" and "generate_data.R" are called by other scripts and do not need to be run independently.
- To recreate simulation results: the MSE simulation (setting 0) and simulation studies
1, 2, and 3 are designed to be run on a cluster. To see a single replicate, set 
home_comp_flag = T. To run on a cluster, change directory dir to the appropriate directory.
Note additionally that results are compiled in folders at the end of the simulation; 
the folders should be created before running. Simulation 4 can run on a local computer
and directly outputs the dataframes for analysis.
- Simulations 0 through 3 produce at least one dataframe per replicate. To combine these,
run "combine_data.R". This produces the result outputs to for use in analysis.
- Analysis of the simulations is completed using code in the "Simulations/Analysis" folder.
- To recreate the real data analysis, you will need the vitalAperiodic, apachePatientResult,
hospital, patient, and apachePredVar tables from the eICU Collaborative Research Database.
In the "data_analysis" folder, first run "import_eICU.R", adjusting any file paths to access the
data on your computer. The "import_eICU.R" code calls "import_vital.R"; you do not need to run "import_vital.R"" 
separately. Then, run "Analyze_eICU.R" to reproduce the results from the paper.
